t%20to%20enter%20customer%20homes%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20taking%20another%20job%20from%20humans%20%E2%80%94%20training%20robots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20rival%201X%20launched%20a%20new%20AI%20model%20on%20Monday%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhumanoid-robot-companies-us-tesla-figure-1x-agility-apptronik-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI-backed%20startup's%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20said%20would%20allow%20the%20company%20to%20move%20away%20from%20using%20humans%20to%20train%20its%20humanoid%20robot%2C%20Neo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHumanoid%20robot%20companies%2C%20including%201X%2C%20typically%20employ%20armies%20of%20human%20operators%20and%20data%20collectors%20to%20train%20their%20machines%20by%20having%20them%20perform%20tasks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-project-warhol-avatar-data-metaverse-smart-glasses-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eranging%20from%20squatting%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20washing%20dishes%20while%20being%20recorded%20or%20wearing%20sensors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1X%20CEO%20Bernt%20B%C3%B8rnich%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20his%20startup's%20new%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-model-ai-explained-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworld%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20would%20allow%20Neo%20to%20learn%20directly%20from%20video%20captured%20by%20the%20robot%20itself%2C%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20data%20collected%20by%20human%20operators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEssentially%2C%20the%20world%20model%20does%20the%20same%20thing%20as%20the%20operator%20would%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20B%C3%B8rnich%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20expected%20the%20update%20to%20improve%20Neo's%20ability%20to%20generalize%20and%20tackle%20tasks%20it%20has%20not%20encountered%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20unlock%20is%20essentially%20now%20that%20intelligence%20scales%20with%20the%20number%20of%20deployed