ing%20switch%20to%20high%20school%20teaching%20in%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20career%20dissatisfaction%20and%20lack%20of%20clear%20goals%20led%20her%20to%20a%20short-lived%20teaching%20role.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20lessons%20she%20learned%20emphasize%20intentional%20career%20planning%20and%20aligning%20work%20with%20personal%20values.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202024%2C%20five%20years%20into%20my%20career%2C%20I%20made%20a%20drastic%20job%20switch%20that%20I%20would%20soon%20come%20to%20regret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20about%20a%20year%20of%20disenchantment%20at%20my%20workplace%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-relations-execs-share-why-they-quit-agency-world-advice-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleft%20my%20job%20at%20a%20public%20relations%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20become%20a%20high%20school%20English%20teacher.%20I%20took%20a%20nearly%2036%25%20pay%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20concerned%20about%20my%20paycheck%20because%20I%20desired%20a%20more%20meaningful%20and%20impactful%20role.%20I%20soon%20found%20myself%20underprepared%20and%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20switch%2C%20and%20I%20left%20my%20teaching%20role%20after%20my%20first%20semester.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20relied%20on%20my%20savings%2C%20my%20family's%20support%2C%20and%20my%20meager%20earnings%20as%20a%20part-time%20yoga%20teacher.%20My%20then-boyfriend%20and%20I%20got%20engaged%20and%20were%20married%20six%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20we%20co-own%20a%20small%20HVAC%20and%20electrical%20company%2C%20where%20I%20lead%20the%20communications%20and%20marketing%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226eb5694f-750a-439a-a809-34bcd871935d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20were%20aspects%20of%20my%20role%20as%20a%20high%20school%20teacher%20that%20I%20enjoyed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20getting%20to%20know%20the%20students%20and%20having%20the%20opportunity%20to%20mentor%20some%20of%20them.%2